*Any* treaty requires ratification by the Senate (not by Congress).

The recourse by the electorate would be to elect a new executive who
would denounce the treaty, that is formally give notice of US
withdrawal. What would happen if the treaty did not allow for
withdrawal is an interesting question.

Or it *would* be an interesting question if there were any
possibility of the situation arising The possibility of the President
negotiating, and the Senate ratifying, such a treaty in the first
place is about the same as the possibility of you going up Niagara
Falls in a barrel.

